-- AMR, US Airways Said to Plan to Fight U.S. Suit to Block Merger
-- B y   M a r y   S c h l a n g e n s t e i n
-- 2013-08-13T16:23:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-13/amr-us-airways-said-to-plan-to-fight-u-s-suit-to-block-merger.html
AMR Corp. (AAMRQ) ’s American Airlines and  US
Airways Group Inc. (LCC)  plan to oppose a U.S. Justice Department
lawsuit seeking to block their $14 billion merger, a person
familiar with the matter said.  The carriers’ decision will be announced later today, said
the person, who asked not to be identified because the details
aren’t public yet.  Ed Stewart, a spokesman for US Airways, and American
spokesman Michael Trevino had no immediate comment on the
Justice Department’s suit.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mary Schlangenstein in Dallas at 
